underlines the importance of personality
development the process of personality
development requires a set of skills
that need to be learned and at times
unlearned basic types of personality
first type of personality is the leader
positive traits of a leader people with
such personality are usually very
independent direct and to-the-point
they have an entrepreneurial streak and
don't mind taking a risk in order to
achieve what they want they enjoy change
and are very focused and intensive
negative traits of a leader
one of the biggest fears such people
face is routine regular activity and
schedule bores them they're also very
fast in what they do and expect the same
intensity from others as well this can
make them appear insensitive the second
type of personality is the socializer or
you can say extrovert positive traits of
a socializer are the socializer would
love to travel and be a part of groups
and are often the center of attention
they are often excited and demanding as
a result of being high energy type
they love the limelight and the hype
their personality is supportive of
others as they are directing their
approach negative traits of the
socializer it is important for the
personality to be liked by others and
can easily hurt if they think someone
doesn't care for them they may take it
very personally and they can be fickle
minded and emotionally weak the third
type of personality is the perfectionist
positive traits of a perfectionist these
people thrive on details accuracy and
take just about everything seriously
they are usually very neat and are very
calculated and precise in everything
they do they're very consistent in
everything they do
because everything has an order or
procedure thus they can be predictable
at times and often very dependable they
are deep thoughtful and usually very
sensitive the know hand why things are
the way they are rather than talking
anything at face value negative traits
of a perfectionist don't expect them to
make a decision real quick as it will
only come after they have checked all
the facts and are satisfied that
everything is correct they spent too
much time with details which can affect
the work schedules now last but not the
least the hermit or you can say
introvert positive traits of a hermit
the typical introvert personality
doesn't like change they prefer to have
a set of guidelines to follow and they
won't mind doing the same thing over and
over they off now very happy and content
with themselves and life in general they
are usually punctual and consistent
negative traits of a hermit as they tend
to keep to themselves such people come
across as shy and arrogant
they are usually disturbed by new
challenges which can affect the
efficiency of their work
